result.execSummary:
The defendant Nichole M Woodruff was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

[MK[ cases #16CF54, #16CF58, #16CF236, #16CM334 called at 2:18pm. 
Defendant Nichole M Woodruff in court, in custody, with Attorney Jeffrey De La Rosa.  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
The Court reviews the Criminal Case Settlement form with Ms. Woodruff, verifying that she understands and joins in the agreement.    
Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered on Case #16CF54-Count #1, on Case #16CF58-Count #1, and on Case #16CM334-Count #2; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgments of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses the remaining counts [Case #16CF54-Count #2; Case #16CF58-Count #2; Case #16CF236 and its three counts; Case 16CM334-Count #1.]

On Case #16CF54-Count #1, and on Case #16CF58-Count #1, the Court withholds sentence, and places Ms. Woodruff on Probation for 5 years, with conditions:
--[in Case #16CF54-Count #1 only] to serve six months in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/ work-release privileges including for family care, employment and counseling or treatment - subject to the rules of the Sheriff, to commence forthwith 
--the Court authorizes the transfer of the service of this jail term to Walworth County, Rock County or Green County conditional on there being no use of electronic monitoring for service of the jail term
---Ms. Woodruff is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in her system; non-compliance will result in loss of work-release privileges without further process.
--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment

--to be subject to random drug screening
--no presence at any pawn stores or resale shops
--to comply with DNA sample provision upon demand
--to pay costs, fees, assessments and surcharges including the DNA surcharge

Days credit for time already served in Case #16CF54:  40 days 
Days credit for time already served in Case #16CF58: 40 days 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

On Case #16CM334-Count #2 the Court sentences Ms. Woodruff to: 
--serve 90 days in Jail with Work-Release [Huber] privileges for family care, employment and counseling or treatment - subject to the rules of the Sheriff, to commence forthwith
--the Court authorizes the transfer of the service of this jail term to Walworth County, Rock County or Green County conditional on there being no use of electronic monitoring for service of the jail term
---Ms. Woodruff is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in her system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber/ work-release privileges without further process.
--to pay costs, fees, assessments, and surcharges including the DNA surcharge and the Domestic Abuse surcharge; this amount is to be entered as a civil judgment
